  <p><strong>Through the zodiac lens:</strong> The Ox's defining trait &mdash; unyielding determination &mdash; is unmistakable in Margaret Thatcher and Malala Yousafzai. Thatcher, the "Iron Lady," embodied the Ox's stubbornness and refusal to yield under pressure, governing with a conviction that reshaped British politics. As a Wood Ox, her Wood element added growth-oriented ambition to the Ox's earthy resolve. Malala, a Fire Ox, channelled the Ox's courage into a different arena: after surviving an assassination attempt at age fifteen, she continued her campaign for girls' education with the kind of unshakeable perseverance that defines this sign.</p>
</section>

<section id="tiger">
