  <p>The Tiger holds the third position, associated with the Earthly Branch <span class="chinese-char">寅</span> (Yin) and carrying hidden Wood, Fire, and Earth. Classical traits emphasise <strong>courage, authority, passion, and unpredictability</strong>. Tigers are natural leaders who command attention, thrive on challenge, and resist being controlled. Their boldness can inspire or intimidate in equal measure.</p>
